Handles the ICE servers received based on the options set by user and parses the differences for iceServer format for cross-browsers.
Format of an ICE server: - STUN is structured like { url: 'stun:hosturl' }. - TURN is structured like { url: 'turn:username@hosturl', credential: 'xxx' } and { url: 'turn:hosturl', username: 'username', credential: 'xxx' } for Firefox browsers.

The ICE server url. For TURN server,
  the format may vary depending on the support of the TURN url format.

return.description:
The updated ICE servers list. - (#index) : type JSON
The ICE server. - (#index).credential : type String
The ICE server credential (password). Only used in TURN servers. - (#index).url : type String
The ICE server url. For TURN server, the format may vary depending on the support of the TURN url format. - (#index).username : type String
The ICE server username. Only used in TURN servers for Firefox browsers.

return.description:
The self user streaming configuration and custom data. - userData : type String | JSON
The custom data. - agent : type JSON
The user's browser agent information. - agent.name : type String
The user's browser agent name. - agent.version : type Integer
The user's browser agent version. - agent.webRTCType : type String
The user's browser webrtc implementation type. - streams : type JSON
The list of peer connections streaming. - streams.(#peerId) : type JSON
The peer connection streaming information. - streams.(#peerId).audio : type JSON|Boolean
The audio streaming information. If there is no stream connection with the peer, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).audio.stereo : type Boolean
The flag that indicates if stereo is enabled for this connection. By default, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).audio.sourceId : type String
The audio MediaStreamTrack source used for this connection. - streams.(#peerId).video : type JSON|Boolean
The video streaming information. If there is no stream connection with the peer, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution : type JSON
The video stream resolution. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution.width : type Integer
The video stream resolution height. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution.height : type Integer
The video stream resolution width. - streams.(#peerId).video.frameRate : type Integer
The video stream resolution framerate. - streams.(#peerId).video.sourceId : type String
The video MediaStreamTrack source used for this connection. - streams.(#peerId).status : type JSON
The MediaStreamTracks enabled status (muted/unmuted). - streams.(#peerId).status.audioMuted : type Boolean
The audio MediaStreamTrack enabled status (muted/unmuted). - streams.(#peerId).status.audioMuted : type Boolean
The video MediaStreamTrack enabled status (muted/unmuted). - bandwidth : type JSON
The bandwidth configuration for the peer connections. This does fixes the bandwidth but doesn't prevent alterations done by browser for smoother streaming. - bandwidth.data : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for data stream. - bandwidth.video : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for video stream. - bandwidth.audio : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for audio stream.

The source id of the audio MediaStreamTrack
   used for this connection.

props.name: video
props.description:
The video stream configuration.
   If parsed as a boolean, other configuration settings under the video
   configuration would be set as the default setting in the connection.

props.name: video.sourceId
props.description:
The source id of the video MediaStreamTrack
   used for this connection.

props.name: status.audioMuted
props.description:
The flag that indicates if audio is muted.
   If audio is set to false, this would be set as true.

props.name: status.videoMuted
props.description:
The flag that indicates if video is muted.
   If video is set to false, this would be set as true.

props.name: bandwidth
props.description:
The bandwidth configuration the peer connections.
   This does fixes the bandwidth but doesn't prevent alterations done by browser for smoother streaming.

props.name: audio
props.description: The bandwidth configuration for the audio stream.

props.name: video
props.description: The bandwidth configuration for the video stream.

props.name: data
props.description: The bandwidth configuration for the data stream.

props.name: SDPType
props.description: The session description type that the peer connection would send. Types are "offer" or "answer".

The shared peer connection id to retrieve

return.description:
The user streaming configuration and custom data. - userData : type String | JSON
The custom data. - agent : type JSON
The user's browser agent information. - agent.name : type String
The user's browser agent name. - agent.version : type Integer
The user's browser agent version. - agent.webRTCType : type String
The user's browser webrtc implementation type. - streams : type JSON
The list of peer connections streaming. - streams.(#peerId) : type JSON
The peer connection streaming information. - streams.(#peerId).audio : type JSON|Boolean
The audio streaming information. If there is no stream connection with the peer, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).audio.stereo : type Boolean
The flag that indicates if stereo is enabled for this connection. By default, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).audio.sourceId : type String
The audio MediaStreamTrack source used for this connection. - streams.(#peerId).video : type JSON|Boolean
The video streaming information. If there is no stream connection with the peer, it's false. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution : type JSON
The video stream resolution. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution.width : type Integer
The video stream resolution height. - streams.(#peerId).video.resolution.height : type Integer
The video stream resolution width. - streams.(#peerId).video.frameRate : type Integer
The video stream resolution framerate. - streams.(#peerId).video.sourceId : type String
The video MediaStreamTrack source used for this connection. - streams.(#peerId).status : type JSON
The MediaStreamTracks enabled status (muted/unmuted). - streams.(#peerId).status.audioMuted : type Boolean
The audio MediaStreamTrack enabled status (muted/unmuted). - streams.(#peerId).status.audioMuted : type Boolean
The video MediaStreamTrack enabled status (muted/unmuted). - bandwidth : type JSON
The bandwidth configuration for the peer connections. This does fixes the bandwidth but doesn't prevent alterations done by browser for smoother streaming. - bandwidth.data : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for data stream. - bandwidth.video : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for video stream. - bandwidth.audio : type Integer
The bandwidth configuration for audio stream.

params.description: Test if TURN servers are parsed correctly for Firefox and Chrome.
Test when TURN is disabled to not return TURN servers.
Test when TURN is enabled to return TURN servers.
Test when STUN is disabled to not return STUN servers.
Test when STUN is enabled to return STUN servers.

example:
test: parseICEServers()
  plan: parseICEServers() : TURN is disabled
  plan: parseICEServers() : TURN is enabled
  plan: parseICEServers() : STUN is disabled
  plan: parseICEServers() : STUN is enabled
